60x2452+0+133/resize/900/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F2c%2Faa%2F68aab37a4f45becaa9830e14f43f%2Flk-layoffs-gettyimages-2168060407.jpg 900w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/4360x2452+0+133/resize/1200/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F2c%2Faa%2F68aab37a4f45becaa9830e14f43f%2Flk-layoffs-gettyimages-2168060407.jpg 1200w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/4360x2452+0+133/resize/1600/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F2c%2Faa%2F68aab37a4f45becaa9830e14f43f%2Flk-layoffs-gettyimages-2168060407.jpg 1600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/4360x2452+0+133/resize/1800/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F2c%2Faa%2F68aab37a4f45becaa9830e14f43f%2Flk-layoffs-gettyimages-2168060407.jpg 1800w" data-template="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/4360x2452+0+133/resize/{width}/quality/{quality}/format/{format}/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F2c%2Faa%2F68aab37a4f45becaa9830e14f43f%2Flk-layoffs-gettyimages-2168060407.jpg" sizes="(min-width: 1025px) 650px, calc(100vw - 30px)" class="img" type="image/jpeg" /&gt;             &lt;img src="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/4360x2452+0+133/resize/1100/quality/50/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F2c%2Faa%2F68aab37a4f45becaa9830e14f43f%2Flk-layoffs-gettyimages-2168060407.jpg" data-template="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/4360x2452+0+133/resize/{width}/quality/{quality}/format/{format}/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F2c%2Faa%2F68aab37a4f45becaa9830e14f43f%2Flk-layoffs-gettyimages-2168060407.jpg" class="img" alt="Illustration of a person in a business suit standing with a blank expression and staring directly at the viewer while standing on top of a large wall clock with a green border." loading="lazy" /&gt;         &lt;/picture&gt; &lt;/div&gt; &lt;div class="credit-caption"&gt;     &lt;div class="caption-wrap"&gt;         &lt;div class="caption" aria-label="Image caption"&gt;             &lt;p&gt;                 Whether you saw it coming or were completely blindsided, getting laid off is one of the most stressful experiences in life. Career coach Octavia Goredema offers concrete advice on both logistical and emotional next steps.                 &lt;b class="credit" aria-label="Image credit"&gt;                                          Westend61/Getty Images                                      &lt;/b&gt;                 &lt;b class="hide-caption"&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;             &lt;/p&gt;         &lt;/div&gt;               &lt;b class="toggle-caption"&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;     &lt;/div&gt;       &lt;/div&gt;    &lt;/div&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Getting laid off can be a devastating experience, and it can make planning for the future difficult. Career coach Octavia Goredema offers a practical &lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/2025/06/25/nx-s1-5366671/layoffs-job-loss-unemployment-finance-money-tips" target="_blank"&gt;checklist of next steps to help you&lt;/a&gt; focus on your future rather than get bogged down by logistics. &lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;ul class="edTag"&gt;&lt;li&gt;💼 Be sure to thoroughly review your exit paperwork. If you need more time during the process, don't hesitate to ask for it. Negotiate your terms; you might be able to secure a longer timeframe for receiving certain benefits.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;💼 Apply for unemployment insurance. The state-run benefit will pay you a weekly amount based on how much you earned before filing for unemployment.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;💼 Take time to reflect on what you want to do next. It can help to think about what you liked and disliked about your last job. This can help you focus your search.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;💼 Create a monthly budget based on a realistic timeline for securing a new job. For instance, if you anticipate that finding your next job will take six months, divide your savings to cover expenses over a six-month timeframe.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;   &lt;p&gt;For more guidance on how to get back on your feet after a layoff, &lt;a href="https://one.npr.org/?sharedMediaId=nx-s1-5366671:g-s1-74379" target="_blank"&gt;listen to this episode of NPR's &lt;em&gt;Life Kit&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/a&gt;. Subscribe to &lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/newsletter/life-kit" target="_blank"&gt;the &lt;em&gt;Life Kit &lt;/em&gt;newsletter&lt;/a&gt; for expert advice on love, money, relationships and more.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;h3 class="edTag"&gt;Weekend picks&lt;/h3&gt;   &lt;div id="res1269518284" class="bucketwrap image large"&gt;             &lt;div     class="imagewrap has-source-dimensions"     data-crop-type=""     style="         --source-width: 3834;         --source-height: 2157;     " &gt;         &lt;picture&gt;             &lt;source srcset="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/3834x2157+0+0/resize/400/quality/85/format/webp/?url=https%3A%2F%2Fmedia.npr.org%2Fassets%2Fimg%2F2025%2F06%2F24%2Frev-1-apex-138_ttrv2_high_res_jpeg_wide.jpeg 400w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/3834x2157+0+0/resize/600/quality/85/format/webp/?url=https%3A%2F%2Fmedia.npr.org%2Fassets%2Fimg%2F2025%2F06%2F24%2Frev-1-apex-138_ttrv2_high_res_jpeg_wide.jpeg 600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/3834x2157+0+0/resize/800/quality/85/format/webp/?url=https%3A%2F%2Fmedia.npr.org%2Fassets%2Fimg%2F2025%2F06%2F24%2Frev-1-apex-138_ttrv2_high_res_jpeg_wide.jpeg 800w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/3834x2157+0+0/resize/900/quality/85/format/webp/?url=https%3A%2F%2Fmedia.npr.org%2Fassets%2Fimg%2F2025%2F06%2F24%2Frev-1-apex-138_ttrv2_high_res_jpeg_wide.jpeg 900w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/3834x2157+0+0/resize/120