tps%3A%2F%2Fmedia.npr.org%2Fassets%2Fimg%2F2025%2F06%2F24%2Frev-1-apex-138_ttrv2_high_res_jpeg_wide.jpeg 1200w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/3834x2157+0+0/resize/1600/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=https%3A%2F%2Fmedia.npr.org%2Fassets%2Fimg%2F2025%2F06%2F24%2Frev-1-apex-138_ttrv2_high_res_jpeg_wide.jpeg 1600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/3834x2157+0+0/resize/1800/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=https%3A%2F%2Fmedia.npr.org%2Fassets%2Fimg%2F2025%2F06%2F24%2Frev-1-apex-138_ttrv2_high_res_jpeg_wide.jpeg 1800w" data-template="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/3834x2157+0+0/resize/{width}/quality/{quality}/format/{format}/?url=https%3A%2F%2Fmedia.npr.org%2Fassets%2Fimg%2F2025%2F06%2F24%2Frev-1-apex-138_ttrv2_high_res_jpeg_wide.jpeg" sizes="(min-width: 1025px) 650px, calc(100vw - 30px)" class="img" type="image/jpeg" /&gt;             &lt;img src="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/3834x2157+0+0/resize/1100/quality/50/format/jpeg/?url=https%3A%2F%2Fmedia.npr.org%2Fassets%2Fimg%2F2025%2F06%2F24%2Frev-1-apex-138_ttrv2_high_res_jpeg_wide.jpeg" data-template="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/3834x2157+0+0/resize/{width}/quality/{quality}/format/{format}/?url=https%3A%2F%2Fmedia.npr.org%2Fassets%2Fimg%2F2025%2F06%2F24%2Frev-1-apex-138_ttrv2_high_res_jpeg_wide.jpeg" class="img" alt="Damson Idris and Brad Pitt in F1 The Movie." loading="lazy" /&gt;         &lt;/picture&gt;          &lt;/div&gt; &lt;div class="credit-caption"&gt;     &lt;div class="caption-wrap"&gt;         &lt;div class="caption" aria-label="Image caption"&gt;             &lt;p&gt;                 Damson Idris and Brad Pitt in &lt;em&gt;F1 The Movie&lt;/em&gt;.                 &lt;b class="credit" aria-label="Image credit"&gt;                                          Warner Bros. Pictures                                      &lt;/b&gt;                 &lt;b class="hide-caption"&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;             &lt;/p&gt;         &lt;/div&gt;               &lt;b class="toggle-caption"&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;     &lt;/div&gt;       &lt;/div&gt;      &lt;/div&gt;    &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Check out what &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/sections/culture/" target="_blank"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;NPR&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;strong&gt; is watching, reading and listening to this weekend:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;🍿 Movies:&lt;/strong&gt; Brad Pitt is in the driver's seat, and, with fresh camera tricks, you can feel like you are in the car with him in &lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/2025/06/26/nx-s1-5445230/f1-movie-review-brad-pitt" target="_blank"&gt;&lt;em&gt;F1&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/a&gt;. Plus, &lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/2025/06/26/nx-s1-5443959/in-theaters-this-week-f1-m3gan-2-0-sorry-baby" target="_blank"&gt;two other films hitting theaters&lt;/a&gt; this weekend.&lt;/p&gt;       &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;📺 TV:&lt;/strong&gt; Marvel's fun new series, &lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/2025/06/26/1254804028/marvels-ironheart-suits-up" target="_blank"&gt;&lt;em&gt;Ironheart&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/a&gt;, follows Riri Williams as she tries to fund her inventions, including a suit a lot like what Iron Man used to wear. She falls in with a gang of criminals who rob from the rich.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;📚 Books: &lt;/strong&gt;We are around halfway through the year, which makes it the perfect time for NPR staffers, including me, to tell you all about their favorite 2025 reads so far. This summer edition of &lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/series/1251857292/books-we-love" target="_blank"&gt;Books We Love&lt;/a&gt; includes &lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/2025/06/25/nx-s1-5356144/fiction-books-summer-2025" target="_blank"&gt;fiction&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/2025/06/25/nx-s1-5356146/nonfiction-memoir-books-summer-2025" target="_blank"&gt;nonfiction picks&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;🎵 Music: &lt;/strong&gt;Lorde's fourth album, &lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/2025/06/27/g-s1-74782/lorde-virgin-review" target="_blank"&gt;&lt;em&gt;Virgin&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/a&gt;, confronts her discomforts and insecurities in a humanizing album made by an artist who knows she doesn't have it all figured out, NPR Music editor Hazel Cills says. Plus, more great &lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/sections/all-songs-considered/2025/06/27/g-s1-74778/new-music-friday-lorde-bruce-springsteen" target="_blank"&gt;music that was released at midnight&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;🎭 Theater: &lt;/strong&gt;At London's Palladium theater, the latest production, &lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/2025/06/26/g-s1-74687/evita-balcony-song-rachel-zegler-london-west-end" target="_blank"&gt;&lt;em&gt;Evita&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/a&gt;, is playing through early September. The musical about Argentina's first lady in the 1940s and early 1950s is sparking buzz because the star sings the song "Don't Cry for Me, Argentina" offstage on a balcony over the street.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;❓ Quiz:&lt;/strong&gt; Welp, let's just say it wasn't my week. But, I bet it will be yours. &lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/2025/06/27/g-s1-74635/bezos-sanchez-mamdani-heat-dome-trump" target="_blank"&gt;Give it your best try&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;h3 class="edTag"&gt;3 things to know before you go&lt;/h3&gt;   &lt;div id="resg-s1-74775" class="bucketwrap image large"&gt;             &lt;div     class="imagewrap has-source-dimensions"     data-crop-type=""     style="         --source-width: 6308;         --source-height: 4206;     " &gt;         &lt;picture&gt;             &lt;source srcset="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/6308x4206+0+0/resize/400/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fa4%2F65%2F24fc11eb484b8da9d35348261f7e%2Fgettyimages-2221489897.jpg 400w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/6308x4206+0+0/resize/600/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fa4%2F65%2F24fc11eb484b8da9d35348261f7e%2Fgettyimages-2221489897.jpg 600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/6308x4206+0+0/resize/800/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fa4%2F65%2F24fc11eb484b8da9d35348261f7e%2Fgettyimages-2221489897.jpg 800w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/6308x4206+0+0/resize/900/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fa4%2F65%2F24fc11eb484b8da9d35348261f7e%2Fgettyimages-2221489897.jpg 900w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/6308x4206+0+0/resize/1200/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fa4%2F65%2F24fc11eb484b8da9d35348261f7e%2Fgettyimages-2221489897.jpg 1200w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/6308x4206+0+0/resize/1600/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fa4%2F65%2F24fc11eb484b8da9d35348261f7e%2Fgettyimages-2221489897.jpg 1600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/6308x4206+0+0/resize/1800/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fa4%2F65%2F24fc11eb484b8da9d35348261f7e%2Fgettyimages-2221489897.jpg 1800w" data-template="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/6308x4206+0+0/resize/{width}/quality/{quality}/format/{format}/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fa4%2F65%2F24fc11eb484b8da9d35348261f7e%2Fgettyimages-2221489897.jpg" sizes="(min-width: 1025px) 650px, calc(100vw - 30px)" class="img" type="image/webp" /&gt;             &lt;source srcset="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/6308x4206+0+0/resize/400/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fa4%2F65%2F24fc11eb484b8da9d35348261f7e%2Fgettyimages-2221489897.jpg 400w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/6308x4206+0+0/resize/600/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fa4%2F65%2F24fc11eb484b8da9d35348261f7e%2Fgettyimages-2221489897.jpg 600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/6308x4206+0+0/resize/800/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fa4%2F65%2F24fc11eb484b8da9d35348261f7e%2Fgettyimages-2221489897.jpg 800w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/6308x4206+0+0/resize/900/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fa4%2F65%2F24fc11eb484b8da9d35348261f7e%2Fgettyimages-2221489897.jpg 900w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/6308x4206+0+0/resize/1200/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fa4%2F65%2F24fc11eb484b8da9d35348261f7e%2Fgettyimages-2221489897.jpg 1200w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/6308x4206+0+0/resize/1600/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fa4%2F65%2F24fc11eb484b8da9d35348261f7e%2Fgettyimages-2221489897.jpg 1600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/6308x4206+0+0/resize/1800/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fa4%2F65%2F24fc11eb484b8da9d35348261f7e%2Fgettyimages-2221489897.jpg 1800w" data-template="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/6308x4206+0+0/resize/{width}/quality/{quality}/format/{format}/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fa4%2F65%2F24fc11eb484b8da9d35348261f7e%2Fgettyimages-2221489897.jpg" sizes="(min-width: 1025px) 650px, calc(100vw - 30px)" class="img" type="image/jpeg" /&gt;             &lt;img src="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/6308x4206+0+0/resize/1100/quality/50/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fa4%2F65%2F24fc11eb484b8da9d35348261f7e%2Fgettyimages-2221489897.jpg" data-template="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/6308x4206+0+0/resize/{width}/quality/{quality}/format/{format}/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fa4%2F65%2F24fc11eb484b8da9d35348261f7e%2Fgettyimages-2221489897.jpg" class="img" alt="Kenya&amp;#039;s Faith Kipyegon reacts at the end of her race after taking part in the &amp;quot;Breaking4&amp;quot; event, in an attempt to become the first woman to run a mile in under four minutes, at Stade Charlety on June 26, 2025 in Paris." loading="lazy" /&gt;         &lt;/picture&gt; &lt;/div&gt; &lt;div class="credit-caption"&gt;     &lt;div class="caption-wrap"&gt;         &lt;div class="caption" aria-label="Image caption"&gt;             &lt;p&gt;                 Kenya's Faith Kipyegon reacts at the end of her race after taking part in the "Breaking4" event, in an attempt to become the first woman to run a mile in under four minutes, at Stade Charlety on June 26, 2025 in Paris.                 &lt;b class="credit" aria-label="Image credit"&gt;                                          Emma Da Silva/AFP via Getty Images                                      &lt;/b&gt;                 &lt;b class="hide-caption"&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;             &lt;/p&gt;         &lt;/div&gt;               &lt;b class="toggle-caption"&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;     &lt;/div&gt;       &lt;/div&gt;    &lt;/div&gt;    &lt;ol class="edTag"&gt;&lt;li&gt;Kenya's Faith Kipyegon attempted to become the first woman to run a mile in under 4 minutes yesterday, but her &lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/2025/06/26/nx-s1-5445959/4-minute-mile-kipyegon" target="_blank"&gt;personal best came up short&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Anna Wintour announced yesterday that she would be &lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/2025/06/26/nx-s1-5447474/anna-wintour-vogue-conde-nast" target="_blank"&gt;stepping down as head of editorial content&lt;/a&gt; at American &lt;em&gt;Vogue&lt;/em&gt; after nearly 40 years in the role.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;em&gt;Dune&lt;/em&gt; director Denis Villeneuve has signed on to &lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/2025/06/26/nx-s1-5446011/james-bond-denis-villeneuve-dune-director" target="_blank"&gt;lead the next installment&lt;/a&gt; of the James Bond franchise.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ol&gt;   &lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;This newsletter was edited by &lt;/em&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/people/859721331/suzanne-nuyen"target="_blank"   &gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;Suzanne Nuyen&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;em&gt;.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/div&gt;</description>
