61293.jpg 800w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/2384x1341+0+172/resize/900/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F20%2F11%2F493128ef4c478b73e2c5558c4603%2Fp18849-fp961293.jpg 900w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/2384x1341+0+172/resize/1200/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F20%2F11%2F493128ef4c478b73e2c5558c4603%2Fp18849-fp961293.jpg 1200w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/2384x1341+0+172/resize/1600/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F20%2F11%2F493128ef4c478b73e2c5558c4603%2Fp18849-fp961293.jpg 1600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/2384x1341+0+172/resize/1800/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F20%2F11%2F493128ef4c478b73e2c5558c4603%2Fp18849-fp961293.jpg 1800w" data-template="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/2384x1341+0+172/resize/{width}/quality/{quality}/format/{format}/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F20%2F11%2F493128ef4c478b73e2c5558c4603%2Fp18849-fp961293.jpg" sizes="(min-width: 1025px) 650px, calc(100vw - 30px)" class="img" type="image/jpeg" /&gt;             &lt;img src="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/2384x1341+0+172/resize/1100/quality/50/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F20%2F11%2F493128ef4c478b73e2c5558c4603%2Fp18849-fp961293.jpg" data-template="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/2384x1341+0+172/resize/{width}/quality/{quality}/format/{format}/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F20%2F11%2F493128ef4c478b73e2c5558c4603%2Fp18849-fp961293.jpg" class="img" alt="Foster + Partners&amp;#039; winning design includes a bridge that will feature a cast-glass balustrade inspired by Queen Elizabeth II’s wedding tiara." loading="lazy" /&gt;         &lt;/picture&gt; &lt;/div&gt; &lt;div class="credit-caption"&gt;     &lt;div class="caption-wrap"&gt;         &lt;div class="caption" aria-label="Image caption"&gt;             &lt;p&gt;                 Foster + Partners' winning design includes a bridge that will feature a cast-glass balustrade inspired by Queen Elizabeth II's wedding tiara.&lt;br&gt;                 &lt;b class="credit" aria-label="Image credit"&gt;                                          Foster + Partners                                      &lt;/b&gt;                 &lt;b class="hide-caption"&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;             &lt;/p&gt;         &lt;/div&gt;               &lt;b class="toggle-caption"&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;     &lt;/div&gt;       &lt;/div&gt;    &lt;/div&gt;    &lt;ol class="edTag"&gt;&lt;li&gt;The &lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/2025/06/24/nx-s1-5443940/queen-elizabeth-memorial-london" target="_blank"&gt;winning design for a new memorial&lt;/a&gt; in St. James Park near Buckingham Palace, honoring Queen Elizabeth II, will feature a bridge with a jewel-like, translucent balustrade reminiscent of her wedding tiara.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;A private crew of four &lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/2025/06/25/nx-s1-5444796/axiom-space-ax-4-launch-iss" target="_blank"&gt;launched into orbit on a SpaceX Falcon 9&lt;/a&gt; rocket Wednesday from the Kennedy Space Center in Florida for a two-week mission.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;TikTok recently banned the hashtag #SkinnyTok after European regulators cautioned that it promoted unrealistic body images and extreme weight loss. Despite the ban, unhealthy information on achieving extreme thinness &lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/sections/shots-health-news/2025/06/24/nx-s1-5438391/tiktok-body-image-diet" target="_blank"&gt;continues to spread on social media&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ol&gt;   &lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;This newsletter was edited by &lt;/em&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/people/859721331/suzanne-nuyen"target="_blank"   &gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;Suzanne Nuyen&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/div&gt;</description>
