      <title>Key takeaways from the U.S. airstrikes on Iran. And, how Iran could respond</title>
      <author>Brittney Melton</author>
      <link>https://www.npr.org/2025/06/23/g-s1-74020/up-first-newsletter-iran-israel-us-airstrikes</link>
      <comments>https://text.npr.org/2025/06/23/g-s1-74020/up-first-newsletter-iran-israel-us-airstrikes</comments>
      <guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.npr.org/2025/06/23/g-s1-74020/up-first-newsletter-iran-israel-us-airstrikes</guid>
      <pubDate>Mon, 23 Jun 2025 11:01:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <description>&lt;div id="storytext" class="storytext storylocation linkLocation"&gt;       &lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Good morning. You're reading the Up First newsletter. &lt;/em&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/newsletter/news" target="_blank"&gt;Subscribe&lt;/a&gt;&lt;em&gt; here to get it delivered to your inbox, and &lt;/em&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/podcasts/510318/up-first/" target="_blank"&gt;listen&lt;/a&gt;&lt;em&gt; to the Up First podcast for all the news you need to start your day.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;h3 class="edTag"&gt;Today's top stories&lt;/h3&gt;   &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Trump administration is defending its decision to strike three nuclear targets in Iran over the weekend.&lt;/strong&gt; U.S. officials say the strikes, which were &lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/2025/06/22/nx-s1-5441731/iran-strike-congress-reaction-vance-rubio" target="_blank"&gt;carried out without congressional approval&lt;/a&gt; and without notifying top Democratic lawmakers, were intended to prevent Iran from developing a nuclear weapon. The United States' decision to intervene came a little over a week after Israel launched a series of strikes on Iran. U.S. officials say the American strikes devastated Iran's nuclear program, but independent experts analyzing satellite imagery say it is &lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/2025/06/22/nx-s1-5441734/satellites-show-damage-iran-nuclear-program-not-destroyed-experts-say" target="_blank"&gt;far from destroyed&lt;/a&gt;. Here are &lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/2025/06/23/nx-s1-5441791/takeaways-us-airstrikes-iran-nuclear-trump" target="_blank"&gt;four takeaways from the U.S. airstrikes&lt;/a&gt; on Iran.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div id="resg-s1-73967" class="bucketwrap image large"&gt;             &lt;div     class="imagewrap has-source-dimensions"     data-crop-type=""     style="         --source-width: 2143;         --source-height: 1205;     " &gt;         &lt;picture&gt;             &lt;source srcset="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/2143x1205+272+225/resize/400/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F76%2F05%2F24834c3a4d9b895caa9480eaa002%2Fgettyimages-2220762372.jpg 400w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/2143x1205+272+225/resize/600/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F76%2F05%2F24834c3a4d9b895caa9480eaa002%2Fgettyimages-2220762372.jpg 600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/2143x1205+272+225/resize/800/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F76%2F05%2F24834c3a4d9b895caa9480eaa002%2Fgettyimages-2220762372.jpg 800w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/2143x1205+272+225/resize/900/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F76%2F05%2F24834c3a4d9b895caa9480eaa002%2Fgettyimages-2220762372.jpg 900w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/2143x1205+272+225/resize/1200/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F76%2F05%2F24834c3a4d9b895caa9480eaa002%2Fgettyimages-2220762372.jpg 1200w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/2143x1205+272+225/resize/1600/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F76%2F05%2F24834c3a4d9b895caa9480eaa002%2Fgettyimages-2220762372.jpg 1600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/2143x1205+272+225/resize/1800/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F76%2F05%2F24834c3a4d9b895caa9480eaa002%2Fgettyimages-2220762372.jpg 1800w" data-template="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/2143x1205+272+225/resize/{width}/quality/{quality}/format/{format}/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F76%2F05%2F24834c3a4d9b895caa9480eaa002%2Fgettyimages-2220762372.jpg" sizes="(min-width: 1025px) 650px, calc(100vw - 30px)" class="img" type="image/webp" /&gt;             &lt;source srcset="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/2143x1205+272+225/resize/400/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F76%2F05%2F24834c3a4d9b895caa9480eaa002%2Fgettyimages-2220762372.jpg 400w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/2143x1205+272+225/resize/600/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F76%2F05%2F24834c3a4d9b895caa9480eaa002%2Fgettyimages-2220762372.jpg 600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/2143x1205+272+225/resize/800/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F76%2F05%2F24834c3a4d9b895caa9480eaa002%2Fgettyimages-2220762372.jpg 800w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/2143x1205+272+225/resize/900/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F76%2F05%2F24834c3a4d9b895caa9480eaa002%2Fgettyimages-2220762372.jpg 900w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/2143x1205+272+225/resize/1200/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F76%2F05%2F24834c3a4d9b895caa9480eaa002%2Fgettyimages-2220762372.jpg 1200w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/2143x1205+272+225/resize/1600/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F76%2F05%2F24834c3a4d9b895caa9480eaa002%2Fgettyimages-2220762372.jpg 1600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/2143x1205+272+225/resize/1800/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F76%2F05%2F24834c3a4d9b895caa9480eaa002%2Fgettyimages-2220762372.jpg 1800w" data-template="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/2143x1205+272+225/resize/{width}/quality/{quality}/format/{format}/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F76%2F05%2F24834c3a4d9b895caa9480eaa002%2Fgettyimages-2220762372.jpg" sizes="(min-width: 1025px) 650px, calc(100vw - 30px)" class="img" type="image/jpeg" /&gt;             &lt;img src="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/2143x1205+272+225/resize/1100/quality/50/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F76%2F05%2F24834c3a4d9b895caa9480eaa002%2Fgettyimages-2220762372.jpg" data-template="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/2143x1205+272+225/resize/{width}/quality/{quality}/format/{format}/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F76%2F05%2F24834c3a4d9b895caa9480eaa002%2Fgettyimages-2220762372.jpg" class="img" alt="Iranian protesters chant slogans and one holds a poster with a vampire-like illustration of President Trump in Tehran&amp;#039;s Revolution Square on Sunday to protest the U.S. attacks on nuclear sites in Iran." loading="lazy" /&gt;         &lt;/picture&gt; &lt;/div&gt; &lt;div class="credit-caption"&gt;     &lt;div class="caption-wrap"&gt;         &lt;div class="caption" aria-label="Image caption"&gt;             &lt;p&gt;                 Iranian protesters chant slogans and one holds a poster with a vampire-like illustration of President Trump in Tehran's Revolution Square on Sunday to protest the U.S. attacks on nuclear sites in Iran.                 &lt;b class="credit" aria-label="Image credit"&gt;                                          Getty Images/Getty Images Europe                                      &lt;/b&gt;                 &lt;b class="hide-caption"&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;             &lt;/p&gt;         &lt;/div&gt;               &lt;b class="toggle-caption"&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;     &lt;/div&gt;       &lt;/div&gt;    &lt;/div&gt;    &lt;ul class="edTag"&gt;&lt;li&gt;🎧 &lt;strong&gt;Democrats have been highly critical of the strikes, while most Republicans have stood by the president&lt;/strong&gt;, NPR's Deepa Shivaram tells&lt;em&gt; Up First&lt;/em&gt;. A few Republicans have said the White House's decision was unconstitutional because it's Congress, not the president, who has the authority to approve the use of force. One public opinion poll from before the U.S. strike on Iran shows that most Americans think the U.S. military shouldn't get involved in the conflict. Trump, who campaigned on the U.S. not getting involved in more foreign wars, raised the idea on social media that there could be a &lt;a href="https://one.npr.org/?sharedMediaId=1254614596:1269507729" target="_blank"&gt;regime change in Iran&lt;/a&gt;, which could potentially get the U.S. more involved.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;       &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Yesterday, Israeli Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu stated that Israel will not be dragged into a war of attrition&lt;/strong&gt;, nor will it end the conflict until its objectives are achieved. Israel wants to degrade Iran's missiles and nuclear program. &lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;ul class="edTag"&gt;&lt;li&gt;🎧&lt;strong&gt; NPR's Hadeel Al-Shalchi, who is in Tel Aviv, says Iran's first move after the U.S. bombed its nuclear sites was to fire missiles towards Israel&lt;/strong&gt;, which she was able to record from her home. Al-Shalchi visited the affluent neighborhood of Ramat Aviv, where one of the missiles hit, and heard from the community. She says people there are &lt;a href="https://one.npr.org/?sharedMediaId=1254614596:1269507729" target="_blank"&gt;overwhelmingly in support of the war&lt;/a&gt;, saying that Iran "has posed an existential threat to Israel with its nuclear program for decades and Israel had to do something about it." The fear in Israel is that the war will result in routine fire with Iran for a long time.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;   &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Iran is now considering how it wants to respond to the U.S. attack on its nuclear program&lt;/strong&gt;, and how it might do that. Iran's Revolutionary Guards released a video overnight saying the U.S. will face consequences and ending with a message saying the U.S. "can start this war, but we'll be the ones who end it." &lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;       &lt;ul class="edTag"&gt;&lt;li&gt;🎧&lt;strong&gt; Iran has a range of options when it comes to retaliating against the U.S.&lt;/strong&gt;, including carrying out a cyber attack and disrupting oil shipping in the Gulf, NPR's Greg Myre says. Iran is in a very difficult position as it's already on the losing end of the battle with Israel. If Iran doesn't respond to the U.S., it will look weak. But if it does respond, Iran could &lt;a href="https://one.npr.org/?sharedMediaId=1254614596:1269507729" target="_blank"&gt;face a larger hit from the U.S.&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;   &lt;h3 class="edTag"&gt;Today's listen&lt;/h3&gt;   &lt;div id="resg-s1-73805" class="bucketwrap image large"&gt;             &lt;div     class="imagewrap has-source-dimensions"     data-crop-type=""     style="         --source-width: 7616;         --source-height: 4284;     " &gt;         &lt;picture&gt;             &lt;source srcset="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/7616x4284+0+398/resize/400/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F86%2F00%2Fa590d70646c08b1fa89c2a767490%2F250617-npr-jimmyawards-josealvaradojr-0080.JPG 400w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/7616x4284+0+398/resize/600/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F86%2F00%2Fa590d70646c08b1fa89c2a767490%2F250617-npr-jimmyawards-josealvaradojr-0080.JPG 600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/7616x4284+0+398/resize/800/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F86%2F00%2Fa590d70646c08b1fa89c2a767490%2F250617-npr-jimmyawards-josealvaradojr-0080.JPG 800w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/7616x4284+0+398/resize/900/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F86%2F00%2Fa590d70646c08b1fa89c2a767490%2F250617-npr-jimmyawards-josealvaradojr-0080.JPG 90