trip/false/crop/7616x4284+0+398/resize/900/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F86%2F00%2Fa590d70646c08b1fa89c2a767490%2F250617-npr-jimmyawards-josealvaradojr-0080.JPG 900w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/7616x4284+0+398/resize/1200/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F86%2F00%2Fa590d70646c08b1fa89c2a767490%2F250617-npr-jimmyawards-josealvaradojr-0080.JPG 1200w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/7616x4284+0+398/resize/1600/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F86%2F00%2Fa590d70646c08b1fa89c2a767490%2F250617-npr-jimmyawards-josealvaradojr-0080.JPG 1600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/7616x4284+0+398/resize/1800/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F86%2F00%2Fa590d70646c08b1fa89c2a767490%2F250617-npr-jimmyawards-josealvaradojr-0080.JPG 1800w" data-template="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/7616x4284+0+398/resize/{width}/quality/{quality}/format/{format}/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F86%2F00%2Fa590d70646c08b1fa89c2a767490%2F250617-npr-jimmyawards-josealvaradojr-0080.JPG" sizes="(min-width: 1025px) 650px, calc(100vw - 30px)" class="img" type="image/jpeg" /&gt;             &lt;img src="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/7616x4284+0+398/resize/1100/quality/50/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F86%2F00%2Fa590d70646c08b1fa89c2a767490%2F250617-npr-jimmyawards-josealvaradojr-0080.JPG" data-template="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/7616x4284+0+398/resize/{width}/quality/{quality}/format/{format}/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F86%2F00%2Fa590d70646c08b1fa89c2a767490%2F250617-npr-jimmyawards-josealvaradojr-0080.JPG" class="img" alt="A billboard showcasing some of this year’s nominees for The National High School Musical Theatre Awards, better known as the Jimmy Awards." loading="lazy" /&gt;         &lt;/picture&gt; &lt;/div&gt; &lt;div class="credit-caption"&gt;     &lt;div class="caption-wrap"&gt;         &lt;div class="caption" aria-label="Image caption"&gt;             &lt;p&gt;                 A billboard showcasing some of this year's nominees for The National High School Musical Theatre Awards, better known as the Jimmy Awards.                 &lt;b class="credit" aria-label="Image credit"&gt;                                          José A. Alvarado Jr. for NPR                                      &lt;/b&gt;                 &lt;b class="hide-caption"&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;             &lt;/p&gt;         &lt;/div&gt;               &lt;b class="toggle-caption"&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;     &lt;/div&gt;       &lt;/div&gt;    &lt;/div&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Tonight is a big night for more than 100 high school theater stars gathered in New York City for the National High School Musical Theatre Awards, also known as the Jimmy Awards. This annual event unites nominees on Broadway to put on a show in just 10 days. The competition begins with around 150,000 students from various schools nationwide, who are ultimately narrowed down to a select group of finalists who will perform at the award ceremony held at the Minskoff Theatre. The top two awards of the night are best actor and best actress in a musical. &lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/2025/06/23/nx-s1-5430901/top-high-school-performers-jimmy-awards" target="_blank"&gt;Read more about the awards&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href="http://one.npr.org/i/nx-s1-5430901:x" target="_blank"&gt;listen to students currently vying&lt;/a&gt; for their chance to take home a Jimmy.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;h3 class="edTag"&gt;Picture show&lt;/h3&gt;   &lt;div id="resg-s1-73630" class="bucketwrap image large"&gt;             &lt;div     class="imagewrap has-source-dimensions"     data-crop-type=""     style="         --source-width: 2208;         --source-height: 1242;     " &gt;         &lt;picture&gt;             &lt;source srcset="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/2208x1242+143+0/resize/400/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F1d%2F13%2F3e2da4804c51a3431154bf3223f2%2Fexterior.jpg 400w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/2208x1242+143+0/resize/600/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F1d%2F13%2F3e2da4804c51a3431154bf3223f2%2Fexterior.jpg 600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/2208x1242+143+0/resize/800/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F1d%2F13%2F3e2da4804c51a3431154bf3223f2%2Fexterior.jpg 800w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/2208x1242+143+0/resize/900/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F1d%2F13%2F3e2da4804c51a3431154bf3223f2%2Fexterior.jpg 900w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/2208x1242+143+0/resize/1200/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F1d%2F13%2F3e2da4804c51a3431154bf3223f2%2Fexterior.jpg 1200w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/2208x1242+143+0/resize/1600/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F1d%2F13%2F3e2da4804c51a3431154bf3223f2%2Fexterior.jpg 1600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/2208x1242+143+0/resize/1800/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F1d%2F13%2F3e2da4804c51a3431154bf3223f2%2Fexterior.jpg 1800w" data-template="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/2208x1242+143+0/resize/{width}/quality/{quality}/format/{format}/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F1d%2F13%2F3e2da4804c51a3431154bf3223f2%2Fexterior.jpg" sizes="(min-width: 1025px) 650px, calc(100vw - 30px)" class="img" type="image/webp" /&gt;             &lt;source srcset="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/2208x1242+143+0/resize/400/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F1d%2F13%2F3e2da4804c51a3431154bf3223f2%2Fexterior.jpg 400w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/2208x1242+143+0/resize/600/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F1d%2F13%2F3e2da4804c51a3431154bf3223f2%2Fexterior.jpg 600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/2208x1242+143+0/resize/800/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F1d%2F13%2F3e2da4804c51a3431154bf3223f2%2Fexterior.jpg 800w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/2208x1242+143+0/resize/900/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F1d%2F13%2F3e2da4804c51a3431154bf3223f2%2Fexterior.jpg 900w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/2208x1242+143+0/resize/1200/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F1d%2F13%2F3e2da4804c51a3431154bf3223f2%2Fexterior.jpg 1200w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/2208x1242+143+0/resize/1600/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F1d%2F13%2F3e2da4804c51a3431154bf3223f2%2Fexterior.jpg 1600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/2208x1242+143+0/resize/1800/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F1d%2F13%2F3e2da4804c51a3431154bf3223f2%2Fexterior.jpg 1800w" data-template="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/2208x1242+143+0/resize/{width}/quality/{quality}/format/{format}/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F1d%2F13%2F3e2da4804c51a3431154bf3223f2%2Fexterior.jpg" sizes="(min-width: 1025px) 650px, calc(100vw - 30px)" class="img" type="image/jpeg" /&gt;             &lt;img src="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/2208x1242+143+0/resize/1100/quality/50/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F1d%2F13%2F3e2da4804c51a3431154bf3223f2%2Fexterior.jpg" data-template="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/2208x1242+143+0/resize/{width}/quality/{quality}/format/{format}/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F1d%2F13%2F3e2da4804c51a3431154bf3223f2%2Fexterior.jpg" class="img" alt="The Wallace Center for Arts and Reconciliation promotes reconciliation, healing, and repair through arts, education, and cultural programming." loading="lazy" /&gt;         &lt;/picture&gt; &lt;/div&gt; &lt;div class="credit-caption"&gt;     &lt;div class="caption-wrap"&gt;         &lt;div class="caption" aria-label="Image caption"&gt;             &lt;p&gt;                 The Wallace Center for Arts and Reconciliation promotes reconciliation, healing, and repair through arts, education, and cultural programming.                 &lt;b class="credit" aria-label="Image credit"&gt;                                          1504                                      &lt;/b&gt;                 &lt;b class="hide-caption"&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;             &lt;/p&gt;         &lt;/div&gt;               &lt;b class="toggle-caption"&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;     &lt;/div&gt;       &lt;/div&gt;    &lt;/div&gt;    &lt;p&gt;In a small town in Shelby County, Ala., — often referred to by the Republican Party as the reddest county in the U.S. — a new museum exhibit is dedicated to Black history. It addresses what happened in Harpersville after enslaved people were emancipated, granted their freedom and not much else. NPR's Picture Show spoke with Tyler Jones, who is part of 1504, the narrative studio behind the project. This studio has been working in collaboration with the Wallace Center for Arts and Reconciliation to reframe the narratives of Black descendant communities through embodied storytelling. Jones highlighted the significance of transforming a plantation from 1841 into a space dedicated to reparative history and healing. Check out this inside &lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/sections/the-picture-show/2025/06/19/nx-s1-5439338/a-former-plantation-becomes-a-space-for-healing-art-and-reparative-history" target="_blank"&gt;look at the project through photos and videos&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;       &lt;h3 class="edTag"&gt;3 things to know before you go&lt;/h3&gt;   &lt;div id="resg-s1-73972" class="bucketwrap image large"&gt;             &lt;div     class="imagewrap has-source-dimensions"     data-crop-type=""     style="         --source-width: 2759;         --source-height: 1839;     " &gt;         &lt;picture&gt;             &lt;source srcset="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/2759x1839+0+0/resize/400/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F09%2F05%2F9792c507427ab97da525ed7d3691%2Fap25174063858008.jpg 400w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/2759x1839+0+0/resize/600/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F09%2F05%2F9792c507427ab97da525ed7d3691%2Fap25174063858008.jpg 600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/2759x1839+0+0/resize/800/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F09%2F05%2F9792c507427ab97da525ed7d3691%2Fap25174063858008.jpg 800w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/2759x1839+0+0/resize/900/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F09%2F05%2F9792c507427ab97da525ed7d3691%2Fap25174063858008.jpg 900w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/2759x1839+0+0/resize/1200/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F09%2F05%2F9792c507427ab97da525ed7d3691%2Fap25174063858008.jpg 1200w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/2759x1839+0+0/resize/1600/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F09%2F05%2F9792c507427ab97da525ed7d3691%2Fap25174063858008.jpg 1600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/2759x1839+0+0/resize/1800/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F09%2F05%2F9792c507427ab97da525ed7d3691%2Fap25174063858008.jpg 1800w" data-template="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/2759x1839+0+0/resize/{width}/quality/{quality}/format/{format}/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F09%2F05%2F9792c507427ab97da525ed7d3691%2Fap25174063858008.jpg" sizes="(min-width: 1025px) 650px, calc(100vw - 30px)" class="img" type="image/webp" /&gt;             &lt;source srcset="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/2759x1839+0+0/resize/400/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F09%2F05%2F9792c507427ab97da525ed7d3691%2Fap25174063858008.jpg 400w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/2759x1839+0+0/resize/600/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F09%2F05%2F9792c507427ab97da525ed7d3691%2Fap25174063858008.jpg 600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/2759x1839+0+0/resize/800/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F09%2F05%2F9792c507427ab97da525ed7d3691%2Fap25174063858008.jpg 800w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/2759x1839+0+0/resize/900/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F09%2F05%2F9792c507427ab97da525ed7d3691%2Fap25174063858008.jpg 900w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/2759x1839+0+0/resize/1200/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F09%2F05%2F9792c507427ab97da525ed7d3691%2Fap25174063858008.jpg 1200w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/2759x1839+0+0/resize/1600/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F09%2F05%2F9792c507427ab97da525ed7d3691%2Fap25174063858008.jpg 1600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/2759x1839+0+0/resize/1800/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F09%2F05%2F9792c507427ab97da525ed7d3691%2Fap25174063858008.jpg 1800w" data-template="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/2759x1839+0+0/resize/{width}/quality/{quality}/format/{format}/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F09%2F05%2F9792c507427ab97da525ed7d3691%2Fap25174063858008.jpg" sizes="(min-width: 1025px) 650px, calc(100vw - 30px)" class="img" type="image/jpeg" /&gt;             &lt;img src="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/2759x1839+0+0/resize/1100/quality/50/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F09%2F05%2F9792c507427ab97da525ed7d3691%2Fap25174063858008.jpg" data-template="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/2759x1839+0+0/resize/{width}/quality/{quality}/format/{format}/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F09%2F05%2F9792c507427ab97da525ed7d3691%2Fap25174063858008.jpg" class="img" alt="Oklahoma City Thunder forward Jalen Williams reacts after making a 3-pointer during the second half of Game 7 of the NBA Finals against the Indiana Pacers on Sunday. The Thunder defeated the Pacers to win their first NBA title since moving to Oklahoma City." loading="lazy" /&gt;         &lt;/picture&gt; &lt;/div&gt; &lt;div class="credit-caption"&gt;     &lt;div class="caption-wrap"&gt;         &lt;div class="caption" aria-label="Image caption"&gt;             &lt;p&gt;                 Oklahoma City Thunder forward Jalen Williams reacts after making a 3-pointer during the second half of Game 7 of the NBA Finals against the Indiana Pacers on Sunday. The Thunder defeated the Pacers to win their first NBA title since moving to Oklahoma City.                 &lt;b class="credit" aria-label="Image credit"&gt;                                          Julio Cortez/AP                                      &lt;/b&gt;                 &lt;b class="hide-caption"&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;             &lt;/p&gt;         &lt;/div&gt;               &lt;b class="toggle-caption"&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;     &lt;/div&gt;       &lt;/div&gt;    &lt;/div&gt;    &lt;ol class="edTag"&gt;&lt;li&gt;The Oklahoma City Thunder have &lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/2025/06/22/nx-s1-5441761/oklahoma-city-thunder-wins-title-nba-finals-indiana-pacers" target="_blank"&gt;won the NBA Finals&lt;/a&gt;, concluding a seven-game series against the Indiana Pacers with a 103-91 victory.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;The Vera C. Rubin Observatory has just released some of its &lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/2025/06/23/nx-s1-5355034/vera-c-rubin-observatory-first-images" target="_blank"&gt;first images to the public&lt;/a&gt;, showing off what it can do before embarking on a 10-year vivid time-lapse video of the night sky.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Bassist Carol Kaye, who worked with Barbra Streisand, Stevie Wonder, The Beach Boys and other hitmakers, said she &lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/2025/06/21/nx-s1-5441080/star-bassist-carol-kaye-rejects-rock-roll-hall-of-fame-honor-inductee-2025" target="_blank"&gt;doesn't want to be inducted&lt;/a&gt; into the Rock &amp; Roll Hall of Fame.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ol&gt;   &lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;This newsletter was edited by &lt;/em&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/people/859721331/suzanne-nuyen"target="_blank"   &gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;Suzanne Nuyen&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/div&gt;</description>
