brucelosttracks1.jpg 600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/3840x2160+0+0/resize/800/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F7e%2F45%2F503a372443f99f60dbfa102ad6a5%2Fbrucelosttracks1.jpg 800w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/3840x2160+0+0/resize/900/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F7e%2F45%2F503a372443f99f60dbfa102ad6a5%2Fbrucelosttracks1.jpg 900w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/3840x2160+0+0/resize/1200/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F7e%2F45%2F503a372443f99f60dbfa102ad6a5%2Fbrucelosttracks1.jpg 1200w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/3840x2160+0+0/resize/1600/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F7e%2F45%2F503a372443f99f60dbfa102ad6a5%2Fbrucelosttracks1.jpg 1600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/3840x2160+0+0/resize/1800/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F7e%2F45%2F503a372443f99f60dbfa102ad6a5%2Fbrucelosttracks1.jpg 1800w" data-template="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/3840x2160+0+0/resize/{width}/quality/{quality}/format/{format}/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F7e%2F45%2F503a372443f99f60dbfa102ad6a5%2Fbrucelosttracks1.jpg" sizes="(min-width: 1025px) 650px, calc(100vw - 30px)" class="img" type="image/jpeg" /&gt;             &lt;img src="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/3840x2160+0+0/resize/1100/quality/50/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F7e%2F45%2F503a372443f99f60dbfa102ad6a5%2Fbrucelosttracks1.jpg" data-template="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/3840x2160+0+0/resize/{width}/quality/{quality}/format/{format}/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F7e%2F45%2F503a372443f99f60dbfa102ad6a5%2Fbrucelosttracks1.jpg" class="img" alt="BruceLostTracks1.jpg" loading="lazy" /&gt;         &lt;/picture&gt; &lt;/div&gt; &lt;div class="credit-caption"&gt;     &lt;div class="caption-wrap"&gt;         &lt;div class="caption" aria-label="Image caption"&gt;         &lt;/div&gt;       &lt;/div&gt;       &lt;/div&gt;    &lt;/div&gt;    &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Check out what &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/sections/culture/" target="_blank"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;NPR&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;strong&gt; is watching, reading and listening to this weekend:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;🍿 Movies: &lt;/strong&gt;The latest Pixar movie,&lt;em&gt; &lt;/em&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/2025/06/19/nx-s1-5438546/new-movies-28-years-later-elio" target="_blank"&gt;&lt;em&gt;Elio&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/a&gt;, follows a lonely 11-year-old orphan who believes that being abducted by aliens is his only path to happiness. Plus, here are two more new movies &lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/2025/06/19/nx-s1-5438546/new-movies-28-years-later-elio" target="_blank"&gt;worth checking out&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;📺 TV:&lt;/strong&gt; From &lt;em&gt;The Waterfront&lt;/em&gt;, which focuses on a family struggling to maintain control of a fishing empire, to &lt;em&gt;King of the Hill &lt;/em&gt;returning after 15 years, these are some &lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/2025/06/17/nx-s1-5434345/the-bear-squid-game-smoke" target="_blank"&gt;shows worth checking out&lt;/a&gt; this summer.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;📚 Books:&lt;/strong&gt; Ready to spice up your life with some mystery and suspense this month? One or &lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/2025/06/18/nx-s1-5435300/summer-books-mystery-fiction" target="_blank"&gt;all four of these new novels&lt;/a&gt; are sure to scratch that itch.&lt;/p&gt;       &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;🎵 Music: &lt;/strong&gt;Next Friday, Bruce Springsteen is releasing seven new records at once, featuring previously unreleased music recorded between 1983 and 2018. To prepare for his upcoming box set, &lt;em&gt;Tracks II: The Lost Albums&lt;/em&gt;, &lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/2025/06/17/nx-s1-5395727/bruce-springsteen-tracks-ii-lost-albums" target="_blank"&gt;take a look at this listening guide&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;🎮 Games: &lt;/strong&gt;NPR's Vincent Acovino attended the Play Days showcase, where he had the opportunity to experience a variety of games, including Resident Evil Requiem and a heist game that took him by surprise. Here's &lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/2025/06/14/g-s1-72240/video-games-resident-evil-requiem-summer-game-fest" target="_blank"&gt;his honest review&lt;/a&gt; of many upcoming titles.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;❓ Quiz:&lt;/strong&gt; Educated guesses and trick questions left me with a barely passing score this week. Are you up for the challenge of passing with flying colors? &lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/2025/06/20/g-s1-73603/labubu-stanley-cup-military-trump-hot-dog-tiktok" target="_blank"&gt;Give it a try&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;h3 class="edTag"&gt;3 things to know before you go&lt;/h3&gt;   &lt;div id="resg-s1-72957" class="bucketwrap image large"&gt;             &lt;div     class="imagewrap has-source-dimensions"     data-crop-type=""     style="         --source-width: 6451;         --source-height: 3629;     " &gt;         &lt;picture&gt;             &lt;source srcset="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/6451x3629+0+336/resize/400/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fd7%2F73%2F202d4a46477e8b3628129443051e%2Fgettyimages-2219308446.jpg 400w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/6451x3629+0+336/resize/600/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fd7%2F73%2F202d4a46477e8b3628129443051e%2Fgettyimages-2219308446.jpg 600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/6451x3629+0+336/resize/800/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fd7%2F73%2F202d4a46477e8b3628129443051e%2Fgettyimages-2219308446.jpg 800w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/6451x3629+0+336/resize/900/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fd7%2F73%2F202d4a46477e8b3628129443051e%2Fgettyimages-2219308446.jpg 900w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/6451x3629+0+336/resize/1200/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fd7%2F73%2F202d4a46477e8b3628129443051e%2Fgettyimages-2219308446.jpg 1200w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/6451x3629+0+336/resize/1600/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fd7%2F73%2F202d4a46477e8b3628129443051e%2Fgettyimages-2219308446.jpg 1600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/6451x3629+0+336/resize/1800/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fd7%2F73%2F202d4a46477e8b3628129443051e%2Fgettyimages-2219308446.jpg 1800w" data-template="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/6451x3629+0+336/resize/{width}/quality/{quality}/format/{format}/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fd7%2F73%2F202d4a46477e8b3628129443051e%2Fgettyimages-2219308446.jpg" sizes="(min-width: 1025px) 650px, calc(100vw - 30px)" class="img" type="image/webp" /&gt;             &lt;source srcset="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/6451x3629+0+336/resize/400/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fd7%2F73%2F202d4a46477e8b3628129443051e%2Fgettyimages-2219308446.jpg 400w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/6451x3629+0+336/resize/600/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fd7%2F73%2F202d4a46477e8b3628129443051e%2Fgettyimages-2219308446.jpg 600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/6451x3629+0+336/resize/800/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fd7%2F73%2F202d4a46477e8b3628129443051e%2Fgettyimages-2219308446.jpg 800w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/6451x3629+0+336/resize/900/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fd7%2F73%2F202d4a46477e8b3628129443051e%2Fgettyimages-2219308446.jpg 900w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/6451x3629+0+336/resize/1200/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fd7%2F73%2F202d4a46477e8b3628129443051e%2Fgettyimages-2219308446.jpg 1200w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/6451x3629+0+336/resize/1600/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fd7%2F73%2F202d4a46477e8b3628129443051e%2Fgettyimages-2219308446.jpg 1600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/6451x3629+0+336/resize/1800/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fd7%2F73%2F202d4a46477e8b3628129443051e%2Fgettyimages-2219308446.jpg 1800w" data-template="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/6451x3629+0+336/resize/{width}/quality/{quality}/format/{format}/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fd7%2F73%2F202d4a46477e8b3628129443051e%2Fgettyimages-2219308446.jpg" sizes="(min-width: 1025px) 650px, calc(100vw - 30px)" class="img" type="image/jpeg" /&gt;             &lt;img src="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/6451x3629+0+336/resize/1100/quality/50/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fd7%2F73%2F202d4a46477e8b3628129443051e%2Fgettyimages-2219308446.jpg" data-template="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/6451x3629+0+336/resize/{width}/quality/{quality}/format/{format}/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fd7%2F73%2F202d4a46477e8b3628129443051e%2Fgettyimages-2219308446.jpg" class="img" alt="Labubu figures and dolls are seen on display at a Pop Mart store on June 9 in Shanghai." loading="lazy" /&gt;         &lt;/picture&gt; &lt;/div&gt; &lt;div class="credit-caption"&gt;     &lt;div class="caption-wrap"&gt;         &lt;div class="caption" aria-label="Image caption"&gt;             &lt;p&gt;                 Labubu figures and dolls are seen on display at a Pop Mart store on June 9 in Shanghai.                 &lt;b class="credit" aria-label="Image credit"&gt;                                          Visual China Group/Getty Images                                      &lt;/b&gt;                 &lt;b class="hide-caption"&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;             &lt;/p&gt;         &lt;/div&gt;               &lt;b class="toggle-caption"&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;     &lt;/div&gt;       &lt;/div&gt;    &lt;/div&gt;    &lt;ol class="edTag"&gt;&lt;li&gt;Labubus have sparked a global frenzy. But how did these plush toys, with their toothy, mischievous grins and furry bodies &lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/2025/06/18/g-s1-72939/what-is-labubu-pop-mart-explained" target="_blank"&gt;become a sensation&lt;/a&gt;?&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Addiction to social media, mobile phones, and video games is associated with an &lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/sections/shots-health-news/2025/06/18/nx-s1-5436951/jama-screens-teens-addiction-suicide-abcd" target="_blank"&gt;increased risk of suicidal thoughts&lt;/a&gt; and behaviors in children, according to a recent study published in JAMA.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Brad Larsen last saw his mom at a New York diner before she suddenly died. Years later, he returned to the diner and shared memories of her with a group of strangers. Among them was a bartender who invited him to sit at the table where he and his mom had last been together. That day, Larsen's unsung heroes provided him with &lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/2025/06/16/nx-s1-5432705/a-new-york-diner-gave-a-moment-for-a-grieving-son-to-remember-his-mother" target="_blank"&gt;the gift of connection&lt;/a&gt; with his mom.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ol&gt;   &lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;This newsletter was edited by &lt;/em&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/people/859721331/suzanne-nuyen"target="_blank"   &gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;Suzanne Nuyen&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/div&gt;</description>
